import cv2
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

image = cv2.imread("/content/drive/MyDrive/Computer Vision - F04/CA1/Description/Pic.jpg")
if image is None:
    print("Error: Image not found or path is incorrect")
else:
    print("Image loaded successfully")
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.show()
    print("Data type:", image.dtype)
    print("Shape:", image.shape)
    if len(image.shape) == 3:
        print("Number of color channels:", image.shape[2])
    else:
        print("Grayscale image (1 channel)")

mean = np.mean(image)
std_dev = np.std(image)

# Calculate contrast
contrast = std_dev / mean if mean != 0 else 0

print(f"Mean Intensity: {mean}")
print(f"Standard Deviation: {std_dev}")
print(f"Contrast: {contrast}")

In[]:
height, width = gray_image.shape

max_diff = 0

for i in range(height - 1):
    for j in range(width - 1):
        diff_h = abs(int(gray_image[i, j]) - int(gray_image[i, j + 1]))

        diff_v = abs(int(gray_image[i, j]) - int(gray_image[i + 1, j]))

        max_diff = max(max_diff, diff_h, diff_v)

print(f"Maximum pixel difference between neighboring pixels: {max_diff}")


diff_map = np.zeros_like(gray_image, dtype=np.uint8)

for i in range(height - 1):
    for j in range(width - 1):
        diff_h = abs(int(gray_image[i, j]) - int(gray_image[i, j + 1]))
        diff_v = abs(int(gray_image[i, j]) - int(gray_image[i + 1, j]))
        diff_map[i, j] = max(diff_h, diff_v)

plt.imshow(diff_map, cmap="hot")
plt.title("Difference Map")
plt.axis("off")
plt.show()

Histogram Equalization

(Histogram Equalization) 2550 .

.

  • .

  • .

  • .

:

  1. ( ) .

  2. CDF (Cumulative Distribution Function) :

$$[ CDF(i) = \sum_{j=0}^{i} Histogram(j) ]$$
  1. CDF . :
$$[ new_pixel(i) = \frac{CDF(i) - CDF_{min}}{(TotalPixels - CDF_{min})} \times (L - 1) ]$$

:

  • ( L ) ( 8 : ( L = 256 ))
  • ( CDF_{min} ) CDF
  • ( TotalPixels )
  1. ( new_pixel(i) ) .
In[]:
equalized = cv2.equalizeHist(gray_image)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plt.imshow(gray_image, cmap='gray')
plt.title("Original Image")
plt.axis("off")

plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plt.imshow(equalized, cmap='gray')
plt.title("Equalized Image")
plt.axis("off")

plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plt.hist(gray_image.ravel(), 256, [0,256])
plt.title("Original Histogram")

plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plt.hist(equalized.ravel(), 256, [0,256])
plt.title("Equalized Histogram")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Histogram Stretching

(Histogram Stretching) () () .

.

( 50 180) :

  • 50 0
  • 180 255

.

$$[ new_pixel = \frac{(pixel - min)}{(max - min)} \times 255 ]$$
In[]:
min_val = np.min(gray_image)
max_val = np.max(gray_image)
print("max value:", max_val)
print("min value:", min_val)
stretched = ((gray_image - min_val) / (max_val - min_val) * 255).astype(np.uint8)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plt.imshow(gray_image, cmap='gray')
plt.title(f"Original Image\nRange: {min_val}-{max_val}")
plt.axis("off")

plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plt.imshow(stretched, cmap='gray')
plt.title("Histogram Stretched Image")
plt.axis("off")

plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plt.hist(gray_image.ravel(), 256, [0,256])
plt.title("Original Histogram")

plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plt.hist(stretched.ravel(), 256, [0,256])
plt.title("Stretched Histogram")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
